<section>
<title>planet.gentoo.org</title>
<body>

<p><b>More fancy desktops: Metisse</b></p>

<!-- add http://www.hboeck.de/uploads/metisse.png to the
gentoo/xml/htdocs/images/gwn/ folder please. Maybe resizing might be a good
thought. -->

<figure link="/images/gwn/20070129_metisse.png" short="Metisse" caption="Metisse
X-Server screenshot" />

<p>
<mail link="hanno@gentoo.org">Hanno Boeck</mail> recently added <uri
link="http://insitu.lri.fr/metisse/">Metisse</uri> to his svn overlay. Metisse
is the answer from <uri link="http://www.mandriva.com">Mandriva</uri> to compiz,
and the whole 3d-desktop thing.
</p>

<p>
Metisse has some some features that gives the possibility to transform the
natural shape of windows. A few examples of this are: rotating, scaling, zooming
your windows. You can even make a parallellogram from your window! Mettisse runs
on its own native X-Server, which is luminocity/xgl-alike and a modified variant
of fvwm.
</p>

<p>
Unfortunately Metisse is still missing an amd64 version, but that is taken care
of upstream. Also we're patiently waitint for a new version where the coders
should fix some known bugs. For more information on where to get the sources,
and how to start the environment, please read the original blog post which
listed below.
</p>

<ul>
<li><uri>http://www.hboeck.de/item/433</uri></li>
<li><uri>http://www.mandriva.com/en/projects/metisse/download</uri></li>
</ul>

</body>
</section>

